div2.entryFree:

      وَبْخَةٌ A burning reproof: (L:) as also ومْخَةٌ;
(IAar;) in which the ب is changed into م
because of the nearness of their places of utterance. (AM.)


      مُسْتَوْفِدٌ (tropical:)  Erecting himself, and not placing
himself at his case, in his manner of sitting;
(L;) i. q. مُسْتَوْفِزٌ. (L, K.)


      2 
      ونّبه, inf. n. تَوْنِيبٌ, He reprehended, reproved, blamed, chid, or reproached, him severely;
&c.: (K:) a dial. form of أَنَّبَهُ. (TA.)
